Manchester City remain favourites to win the Premier League after a critical 3-0 win over Brighton on Wednesday. City scored three times after the break at a nervy Etihad Stadium to move back above Liverpool at the top of the Premier League. They are now 4/9 favourites to win the Premier League after avoiding defeat against rivals Liverpool on Sunday afternoon. The side played out a thrilling 2-2 draw with the Reds. Liverpool, one point behind City, are 13/8 favourites to win the league while Chelsea are 500/1 and in need of a miracle. Pep Guardiola claimed any slip would cost Manchester City the title.